      "role": "user",
      "content": "hey my realtor just mentioned i need to set up an escrow account for the house i'm buying in toronto. i've never heard of that before... what exactly is escrow and why do i need it for the closing?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "An escrow account is a neutral third-party holding place for funds and documents during the home-buying process, ensuring that the buyer's money and the seller's property title are protected until all conditions are met. You need it for closing in Toronto because it acts as a safety net, preventing either party from being left holding the bag if the other side backs out or if there are title issues. It's a standard procedure in real estate transactions to ensure a fair and secure exchange of assets.\n\nThink of it like a bank vault where the transaction details are kept safe until the deal is finalized. Without it, you'd be handing over your life savings directly to a stranger, which is a recipe for disaster. In the real estate world, escrow is the only way to ensure that the buyer gets the keys and the seller gets the cash without any mix-ups.\n\nIt's a bit like a game of musical chairs where the escrow agent is the referee, making sure everyone follows the rules. If you skip this step, you might end up in a situation where you've paid but don't own the house, or the seller has sold the house but hasn't received their money. The escrow process protects both parties from these kinds of unfortunate",
      "source": "target",
